# Git identity

- Do **not** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` or any Cursor attribution to commits pushed to GitHub.
- Use the project identity **94BILLY** / **contact@94billy.com** (or your configured `user.name` / `user.email`) for author and committer when making commits in this repo.
- If the environment injects co-author trailers into `git commit`, use `git commit-tree` with explicit `-m` messages, or amend after disabling the injection in Cursor settings (disable “Add co-author” / similar for Git).
